  <brief_title>Oxytocin Effects on Cytokines and Endocrine Parameters After LPS Induced Systemic Inflammatory Effects in Healthy Volunteers</brief_title>
  <official_title>Oxytocin Effects on Cytokines and Endocrine Parameters After LPS Induced Systemic Inflammatory Effects in Healthy Volunteers</official_title>
  <sponsors>
    <lead_sponsor>
      <agency>Medical University of Vienna</agency>
      <agency_class>Other</agency_class>
    </lead_sponsor>
  </sponsors>
  <source>Medical University of Vienna</source>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The aim of this study is to determine if oxytocin administration is able to blunt LPS induced
      increase of cytokines (TNF-Î±) and if there is a change in the endocrine response after
      lipopolysaccharide administration in humans.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
